Company description: Globus Baumarkt is a leading retail chain in Germany and Luxembourg, specializing in home improvement and gardening supplies. The company offers a comprehensive range of products, including building materials, tools, and garden equipment, catering to the diverse needs of its clientele. With approximately 90 stores and a dedicated workforce of around 9,000 employees, Globus Baumarkt aims to provide an exceptional shopping experience for both DIY enthusiasts and professional tradespeople. The company's mission is to deliver high-quality products at competitive prices while ensuring excellent customer service and expert advice. Globus Baumarkt serves a diverse customer base that includes homeowners, contractors, and gardening aficionados, making it a go-to destination for a wide array of home improvement needs. The company actively engages in training and development, with around 700 apprentices enrolled in various programs, reflecting its commitment to fostering talent within the retail sector. By collaborating with various suppliers and partners, Globus Baumarkt maintains a diverse product range, ensuring customers have access to the latest tools, materials, and gardening supplies. A standout product offering is the Power XChange battery system from Einhell, which promotes flexibility and organization by allowing universal use across all devices in the product family. Globus Baumarkt is also dedicated to sustainability and community engagement, striving to provide innovative solutions that are both cost-effective and environmentally friendly. Through its strong focus on customer service and partnerships with renowned manufacturers, Globus Baumarkt aims to be the first choice for all DIY and construction projects, empowering customers with the knowledge and resources they need to succeed in their endeavors.

We are proud to be known for our excellent project-related services in store and online. Company description: Castorama Polska Sp. z o.o. is a leading retail chain in Poland, specializing in the sale of building materials and accessories for DIY enthusiasts. Headquartered in Warsaw, the company offers a comprehensive range of products and services for home renovation, construction, and gardening, catering to both individual customers and professional contractors. Castorama's mission is to empower customers to create their ideal living spaces by providing quality products at competitive prices, complemented by exceptional customer service. The company is committed to promoting sustainability by offering eco-friendly products and renewable energy solutions, aligning with its ambitious ESG goals, which include reducing CO₂ emissions and increasing the share of sustainable products in its sales.  Castorama engages in responsible business practices and strives to be a market leader by delivering innovative solutions and maintaining high standards of customer satisfaction. Its clientele includes homeowners, DIY enthusiasts, and professionals in the construction industry, reflecting a diverse target market. The company collaborates with suppliers and manufacturers from around the world, leveraging the international expertise and resources of its parent organization, the Kingfisher Group. By focusing on customer needs and sustainability, Castorama aims to be the go-to destination for home improvement in Poland, fostering a community of creativity and responsible living.

Company description: Praxis Doe-Het-Zelf Center B.V. is a leading retailer in the Netherlands, specializing in home improvement and DIY products since its establishment in 1978. The company offers an extensive range of items, including bathroom furniture, kitchen supplies, and garden accessories, aimed at empowering customers to create their ideal living spaces. Praxis's mission is to provide accessible and affordable solutions that enable individuals to undertake their DIY projects with confidence. The company's vision is centered on enhancing the DIY experience through expert advice and high-quality products. Catering to a diverse clientele that includes homeowners, renters, and DIY enthusiasts, Praxis collaborates with various partners to ensure a comprehensive selection of tools and materials. The company is committed to customer satisfaction, offering services such as professional installation, personalized product advice, and tool rental, which further solidifies its position as a go-to destination for all home improvement needs. With a strong focus on sustainability, Praxis aims to support the makers of today and tomorrow, providing not only products but also the knowledge and resources necessary for successful DIY projects. The company operates numerous stores across the Netherlands and is expanding its online platform, ensuring that customers have access to its offerings wherever they are. Through its dedication to quality, service, and customer empowerment, Praxis Doe-Het-Zelf Center B.V. continues to inspire creativity and satisfaction in home improvement endeavors.

Company description: Boels Rental is one of the most renowned rental companies in Europe. We provide our services through an international network of over 750 rental locations in both general and specialist rental. As well as through our network of almost 3000 DIY shop-in-shops. We have a market presence in 17 countries and employ over 7000 employees.  Over the years and thanks to its unlimited drive, the family business has grown into one of Europe’s leading rental organisations. We pride ourselves in our ability to exceed our customers’ expectations with innovative rental equipment. By optimising usage of our extensive range of environmentally friendly equipment in a shared economy and decreasing transport distances, we contribute to a more sustainable world. We provide a full ‘One Stop Shop’ service. Our dense depot network allows us to work efficiently and locally to provide a high level of service and added value to our customers. Boels Rental also has 15 specialized business divisions including Site Preparation, Modular Space, Survey & Laser, Event Service, Power & HVAC, Traffic Service, Industrial Support, Sanitation, Hoisting & Lifting and Access Control.  Our employees have a can-do attitude. Boels thrives on the entrepreneurial spirit of our employees who see themselves as service providers, furthermore as partners to our customers. It’s no surprise that an extremely high number of colleagues feel engaged in the company. At Boels Rental, our moto is “anything is possible and we’ll make it happen”.  Our full range of products, branches and specialties can be found at www.boels.com

Company description: Einhell Germany AG, with over 40 subsidiaries worldwide, has been one of the leading suppliers in the Do-It-Yourself sector for more than 55 years, developing and selling solutions for DIY enthusiasts and hobby gardeners for use in the home, workshop and garden. The company, based in Landau an der Isar in Lower Bavaria, is now active in more than 90 countries. The product range includes hand-held power tools, stationary tools and accessories, as well as products in the field of garden and lawn care, and irrigation and drainage technology. Einhell places particular focus on the further development of its cordless product range in the form of the Power X-Change battery system, which already includes over 250 cordless tools and gardening equipment. Company description: Rusta Finland Oy is a leading retail company in the Nordic low-price market, specializing in a diverse range of home and garden products. Operating under the Rusta brand, the company focuses on providing high-quality items at competitive prices, making home improvement accessible to a broad audience. Rusta's mission is to enable customers to "renew and replenish their homes at surprisingly low prices," while its vision emphasizes becoming the leading and most trusted low-price retailer in Europe. The company serves a wide array of clients, including individual consumers, families, and DIY enthusiasts, primarily through its network of over 200 physical stores and an online sales platform in Finland and other Nordic countries. Rusta's product assortment includes home decoration, consumables, seasonal products, leisure items, and DIY supplies, ensuring a constantly updated selection that meets the evolving needs of its customers. The company is committed to sustainability, integrating eco-friendly practices into its operations and striving for climate neutrality by 2030 for direct emissions and by 2045 for all emissions. Rusta collaborates with various suppliers and partners who adhere to strict environmental and social standards, ensuring responsible sourcing and high product quality. Additionally, Rusta has developed a strong customer loyalty program, Club Rusta, which has seen significant growth and engagement. The company aligns its operations with the UN's Sustainable Development Goals and the UN Global Compact's principles, focusing on environmental responsibility, human rights, and anti-corruption. With a strategic vision for sustainable growth and operational efficiency, Rusta Finland Oy aims to expand its market presence while enhancing customer satisfaction and loyalty through innovative and affordable product offerings.

Company description: Rusta AB is a leading retail company based in Upplands Väsby, Sweden, specializing in a diverse range of home improvement and leisure products. With a focus on enhancing the quality of life for its customers, Rusta continues to adapt its product offerings to market trends while maintaining a strong emphasis on customer satisfaction and operational excellence.

Company description: Clas Ohlson AB is a leading Swedish retail company founded in 1918, specializing in home improvement, DIY, and consumer goods. The company aims to simplify everyday life for its customers by providing a wide range of practical and sustainable solutions at attractive prices. Clas Ohlson offers an extensive assortment of products, including tools, hardware, electrical items, multimedia, and home improvement supplies, available through both physical stores and a robust online platform across Sweden, Norway, and Finland. With a mission to make home fixing accessible, sustainable, and enjoyable for everyone, Clas Ohlson emphasizes sustainability by promoting durable products and offering spare parts to extend the life of items. The company serves a diverse clientele, including DIY enthusiasts, homeowners, and professionals, and has a strong customer base with approximately 5.4 million members in its loyalty program, Club Clas, which enhances customer engagement and satisfaction. Clas Ohlson is committed to responsible growth and aims to achieve a fully circular and climate-neutral business model by 2045, reflecting its dedication to environmental stewardship. The company collaborates with various partners to ensure compliance with ethical sourcing and labor standards, positioning itself as a trusted brand in the retail market. Through continuous innovation and a focus on customer needs, Clas Ohlson strives to maintain its position as a first-choice destination for home fixing solutions. The company also emphasizes corporate governance and risk management, ensuring transparency and accountability while navigating the dynamic retail environment. With a strong emphasis on inclusivity and employee well-being, Clas Ohlson fosters a positive workplace culture that supports growth and development for its co-workers. Overall, Clas Ohlson is dedicated to enhancing customer experience and operational efficiency while promoting environmentally friendly practices throughout its supply chain.

Company description: For almost a century, we have been devoting our passion to improve peoples homes. Our people work hard to create innovative, quality products to help people love where they live work and play. The Fetim Group is an international trading company founded in 1919. We bring you home improvement products on time, as promised. From our distribution centre in Amsterdam, we deliver thousands of products on a daily basis to customers in over 40 countries worldwide. Fetim delivers safe and sustainable products, keeping an eye on the environment. We strive for a good balance between our company, community and our planet. It is up to us to leave a legacy worthy of the generations to come. We are always in search of creative and motivated people to join our team. As a company that is rapidly adapting to new developments, Fetim prides itself to be a pleasant work environment, where we encourage our people to build on their career and, at the same time, have fun while doing it. Being a company with offices and services all over the world, new challenges and opportunities lie ahead of us at all time. Together with a diverse team of people from different backgrounds and countries around the world, we strive for the best. Our people are flexible, independent, creative and inspiring. Fetim is a stable and consistent family business, in other words, the ideal place for employees to develop and grow alongside the company. Fetim’s culture can be described as ambitious, broad-minded and always in search of new opportunities. For us, the obvious is not good enough. We are go-getters, together we make it happen. We are looking for people who align with our vision and want to be part of this exciting journey.

Company description: Ως Praktiker Hellas ξεκινήσαμε την πορεία μας το 1991 και μετράμε περισσότερα από 30 χρόνια παρουσίας στην ελληνική αγορά. Aπο το 2025 είμαστε μέρος του επενδυτικού ομίλου Paval Holding ο οποίος κατέχει τη Dedeman, ηγέτιδα δύναμη στην αγορά DIY της Ρουμανίας και μία από τις μεγαλύτερες επιχειρηματικές εταιρείες της Νοτιοανατολικής Ευρώπης. Αποτελούμε σήμερα το Νo. 1 Ελληνικό Δίκτυο Home Improvement & DIY και one-stop-shop προορισμό για όλες τις ανάγκες του σπιτιού και του κήπου, παρέχοντας καθημερινά 50.000 προϊόντα και ολοκληρωμένες υπηρεσίες, για κάθε μικρή ή μεγάλη αλλαγή! Διαθέτοντας 17 καταστήματα πανελλαδικά, δυναμικό e-commerce και εξειδικευμένο τμήμα Praktiker Business καλύπτουμε το 99% των αναγκών του Σπιτιού για το 100% της Σύγχρονης Κοινωνίας. Αποστολή μας είναι να δίνουμε τη δύναμη σε κάθε σπίτι και κάθε επαγγελματία να βελτιώνει την ποιότητα ζωής του με τα προϊόντα, τις υπηρεσίες & τις DIY λύσεις μας και να παρέχουμε ισότιμη και αξιοπρεπή καταναλωτική εμπειρία προς όλους! Από διαφορετικά μονοπάτια ο καθένας/καθεμιά μας, διαφορετικοί μεταξύ μας αλλά ενωμένοι με το μεράκι μας, είμαστε εδώ για να σχεδιάσουμε και να βρούμε τη λύση ή το προϊόν για κάθε σπίτι, κάθε πελάτη, κάθε επαγγελματία και κάθε ανάγκη. Και όλα αυτά γιατί αγαπάμε το σπίτι μέσα & έξω!  Η ομάδα μας αποτελείται από 1.200 ανθρώπους που κάνουν καθημερινά τη διαφορά, οδηγούν τις αλλαγές, εξελίσσονται και πειραματίζονται. Μαζί τους σχεδιάζουμε το επόμενο σπίτι, την επόμενη επιχείρηση, μια καλύτερη κοινωνία, ένα πράσινο περιβάλλον, το μέλλον τους!

FISHBULL's mission is to serve as a reliable partner for both DIY enthusiasts and professionals, providing them with the essential tools and materials needed for their projects at competitive prices. FISHBULL values partnerships with suppliers and service providers to maintain a wide range of products and services, reinforcing its market position. With a vision to be a leading player in the discount retail sector, FISHBULL is recognized for its commitment to sustainability and quality. The company aims to meet the diverse needs of its clients in various sectors, including construction, gardening, and home improvement, while fostering customer loyalty through a knowledgeable staff and a user-friendly online shopping platform. Overall, FISHBULL Franz Fischer SE & Co. KG is dedicated to providing exceptional value and a pleasant shopping experience, making it a trusted name in the hardware and DIY market.

Company description: OBI Italia è una multinazionale leader nel settore della grande distribuzione organizzata (GDO), specializzata nella fornitura di prodotti per il fai-da-te, la casa e il giardino. Con sede a Cologno Monzese, l'azienda si propone di offrire un'esperienza di acquisto unica e formativa, puntando sull'apprendimento continuo e sullo sviluppo delle competenze dei propri collaboratori attraverso programmi di formazione dedicati. OBI Italia si rivolge a una clientela variegata, che include sia privati che professionisti, e collabora con fornitori di alta qualità per garantire un assortimento completo e innovativo di articoli.  La missione dell'azienda è fornire ai clienti una vasta gamma di prodotti di alta qualità, supportati da un servizio clienti eccellente e soluzioni innovative per migliorare gli spazi abitativi. OBI Italia si distingue per la sua attenzione alla sostenibilità, collaborando con marchi come Energizer per promuovere l'uso di batterie ricaricabili e iniziative di riciclo. L'azienda promuove un ambiente di lavoro dinamico e stimolante, valorizzando l'equilibrio tra vita lavorativa e personale e offrendo vantaggi come sconti per i dipendenti e permessi per la genitorialità. Con una rete di negozi fisici e un'efficiente piattaforma di e-commerce, OBI Italia si impegna a rendere l'esperienza di acquisto semplice e accessibile a tutti. L'azienda è costantemente impegnata a ottimizzare i processi logistici e a migliorare l'efficienza operativa, contribuendo così al successo del proprio business. OBI Italia si posiziona come un punto di riferimento nel settore del fai-da-te e della home improvement, rispondendo alle esigenze di una clientela che cerca prodotti affidabili e sostenibili per i propri progetti.

Company description: Chadwicks Group is Ireland's leading builders' merchanting company, operating with over 50 stores and over 1,400 colleagues across the country.  Thanks to our unrivalled knowledge and expertise in the construction sector, we have been part of the fabric of everyday life in Ireland for over 200 years, providing building materials to homes, hotels, farms, transport networks and every other form of business throughout the country. Our story starts in 1818 when Thomas Heiton set up business in Dublin as a coal importer and distributor meeting the needs of the growing city. In the early 1900s the business diversified, adding a sector specialising in iron products, and from the 1960s onwards, additional products such as timber and plumbing products were added. Our Chadwicks business was founded in 1902 by William Thomas Chadwick at Talbot Place, Dublin, to supply builders' merchants and the major building contractors with cement and plaster produced in Ireland and abroad. During this time all deliveries to Chadwicks' customers throughout Dublin City and County were by horse drawn vehicles. In the early days the firm owned three horses and carts, but as business increased they added a fourth horse and cart and employed another driver! In the '50s the business expaned, moving to bigger premises in Walkinstown and adding new lines such as fire clay to its range of building products. Further expansion took place in the '60s and in 1967 the company opened its first branch outside Dublin, in Kilkenny. Today, Chadwicks is Ireland's leading Builders Merchants and Home Improvement Specialist, offering customers a huge range of timber, building materials and home improvement supplies including plumbing and heating products. Chadwicks Group currently operates Chadwicks, Heiton Steel, The Panelling Centre, Telfords, Cork Builders Providers, Proline, Sitetech, Morgans Timber, HSS Hire Ireland and Davies builders' and plumbers' merchanting businesses in the Republic of Ireland.

Company description: The Freefoam Group is a leading manufacturer of PVC-U and PVC-UE building products including a wide range of fascias, soffits, rainwater systems, external cladding and interior decorative paneling.  The Freefoam Group was founded in Cork, Ireland in 1990 and co-ordinates manufacturing and sales for the Irish and Continental markets. Its subsidiary company in Northampton, Freefoam Plastics (U.K.) Ltd., manages the manufacturing, distribution and sales activities for the UK market.  Distribution for the French and Belgium market is handled from the base in Roeselare, Belgium. Freefoam employs over 200 staff throughout Europe and considers its role within the community as vital to its success. To ensure minimal adverse effects on the local environment the manufacturing process is subjected to continual review. It operates to ISO 9001:2008 quality standards for continuous improvement across all operations, processes and procedures to ensure that its customers receive the highest level of quality and service. Freefoam’s PVC products offer house builders, local authorities, developers and home improvement professionals a high-quality, low-maintenance alternative to conventional timber, backed by industry-leading guarantees. Freefoam’s unbeatable 50-year Lifetime Extended Guarantee is available to Freefoam Registered Installers on white roofline products. This is in addition to a 20-year Lifetime Guarantee as standard on white roofline. White cladding, coloured products and Freefoam’s Woodgrain range also come with a 10-year guarantee as standard.   As a responsible manufacturer, our approach to sustainability aims to monitor and reduce the overall impact of our business activities on the environment. One of our biggest innovation drivers across our operations, is our continued transition from a linear to a ‘Circular Economy’ - enabling the re-use and circulation of resources, retaining economic value, and eliminating waste

Company description: Brilliant AG, based in Gnarrenburg, is a prominent manufacturer of innovative lighting solutions, specializing in both indoor and outdoor products. As a publicly traded subsidiary of the National Lighting Company (NLC), Brilliant AG benefits from strategic collaborations with its parent company and other subsidiaries, such as Poole Lighting Ltd. and Endon Lighting Ltd., to strengthen its market presence. The company is committed to responsible business practices, adhering to legal regulations and ethical guidelines, and expects the same from its employees and partners. Company description: Founded on a passion for craftsmanship and precision tools, Viking Arm was established in Norway by Øivind Resch and Terje Scheen in 2018. Both Øyvind and Terje have long and successful track records as innovators and entrepreneurs. The Viking Arm tool is their first product made for both the professional craftsman and home improvement enthusiast.  “If something’s worth doing, it’s worth doing right”, says a Norwegian proverb. We took this to heart when developing the Viking Arm. Every single detail in the manufacturing process, from the stainless steel parts, aluminum body to the springs that control the lever, has been tested and verified. And then tested and verified again. The result? A completely new tool with specifications and quality that exceed the demands of professionals, yet affordable for handicraft enthusiasts everywhere.  Today, the Viking Arm is rapidly gaining ground in both domestic and international markets. But this is only the beginning.  The Viking Arm is the first of a planned product range of patented precision hand tools, all built with our ingenious combination of innovation and high build quality.  Our business strategy is to stay focused on the path that cultivates our passion for innovation, keeps our product desirable and appreciated and strengthens and differentiates the Viking Arm brand qualities – innovative and lasting design, superior craftsmanship, creativity and an intimate understanding of the professional craftsman’s needs. The company’s Vision is that Viking Arm shall be recognized for its innovation, quality and speed to market. This clearly forms our Mission: “Viking Arm shall develop and deliver radically innovative new tools in the global market’’.  It’s as simple as that.   Viking Arm AS is located in Oslo with a manufacturing facility in Bærum (Greater Oslo).  Feel free to contact us to learn know more about the Viking Arm or to become our distributor.

By collaborating with leading suppliers and leveraging advanced technology, Zanutta is committed to ensuring that its products not only meet but exceed industry standards. The target market encompasses both small enterprises and large corporations seeking reliable protective gear to safeguard their workforce. Through its innovative solutions and unwavering dedication to quality, Zanutta continues to solidify its reputation as a trusted partner in the construction and home improvement industry.

Company description: Like most legacy industries the handyman industry was designed by men, for men - which (whilst deeply problematic), was accepted 60 years ago.  Now the term ‘man of the house’ is thankfully fading into obscurity and women control 80% of global consumer spending (90% in home improvements). But yet the industry is still wildly underserving its majority market. There’s no scarcity of work, but there is a huge deficit of skilled craftspeople. That’s why it takes 6 weeks for a handyman to come to your house, say he doesn’t have the right tools, charge you 100€ and leave. Unsurprisingly, when employment opportunities are only accessible to half the population - standards fall. As customers, we’ve universally accepted such poor standards that if we’re not scammed or sexually harassed, then we consider this an awesome service. In an industry where you’re not just in someone’s home, you’re in their bathroom, in their bedroom, you’re moving their things around and using loud tools - trust, communication, accountability and safety should be at the forefront. Driller Queens solves both of these problems with one platform. We provide underemployed, skilled FLINTA* craftspeople with well-paid flexible work, Creating a workforce that actually understands and serves the needs of our customers. The bar in the Handyman industry is so low it’s practically a trip hazard. And we’re going to raise it. Want to know more? Check out the Arte Documentary about Driller Queens here: https://www.arte.tv/de/videos/104429-013-A/re-nagellack-und-bohrmaschine/

Company description: La Corderie is one of the oldest shops in Brussels still in operation. Created in 1894, the store experienced the invention of Neon, two world wars, the introduction of universal voting rights, the 1958 world exhibition and the sudden rise in real estate prices. Ancient object dating from the Egyptians, the rope is useful to decorate a place, to take someone out of a ditch, to connect a point to another in equilibrium, to climb in the trees, to go down a cliff, to support a platform, to deposit some material in inaccessible places, stretching sails, relaxing muscles or hooking people up. Rope is a niche product that affects many areas. In a former parquet warehouse, located in Ixelles, the Corderie welcomes sailors, architects, decorators, entrepreneurs, scientists, cultural exhibition directors, yogists, pruners, managers purchase of amusement parks, decorators, tightrope walkers, sportsmen, movers, students, animal trainers, magicians  undertakers. The store has constantly renewed the strings of its bow to satisfy the requirements of its customers. This is why La Corderie not only sells rope but also cable, nets, straps, garden equipment, equipment PPE (Personal Protective Equipment), burlap and fittings (pulleys , tensioners, cable clamp, lug, ...). In addition, the vast majority of products sold there are of European origin. This allows him to keep close contact with the suppliers to ensure customer quality of products and the possibility of manufacturing on demand. To meet specific requests, La Corderie has set up, thanks to the fruits oof its expertise, a workshop that makes ropes, ladders, natural coconut mats, nets and custom straps. Managed by an attentive and available team, La Corderie does not hesitate to go to the ropes to meet the varied and sometimes original needs of its customers. The team always aims for excellence in the quality of its products, in the availability with its customers and in the speed of execution.

Company description: AZIENDA Da piu di 70 anni siamo distributori di ferramenta tecnica. Per vocazione ci siamo concentrati sulla fornitura di materiale per serramentisti in legno, ai quali offriamo una gamma di prodotti di qualità per qualsiasi lavorazione. Annoveriamo anche articoli per serramentisti in alluminio, mobilieri e per imprese edili; disponiamo inoltre di un’area espositiva con porte, maniglie, serramenti, blindati e ferramenta al dettaglio. CONSULENZA In questi anni, per sostenere in maniera determinata la nostra crescita, abbiamo investito in professionalità e competenza. Il nostro personale viene regolarmente formato per poter svolgere il proprio ruolo disponendo di informazioniaggiornate sia per quanto riguarda l’evoluzione della tecnologia, sia in materia di innovazione e di normative. Siamo quindi in grado di offrire un servizio di costante aggiornamento e di consulenza a tutti i clienti che puntano sulla qualità e sulla professionalità. PRODOTTI Abbiamo a scaffale oltre 170.000 prodotti, tutti disponibili : ferramenta per serramenti, porte , blindate, maniglie e utensileria. L’area di commercio al dettaglio offre inoltre accessori da bagno, giardinaggio, articoli fai da te, scale, idropulitricie articoli per la casa. SERVIZI A garanzia di un servizio accurato e rapido, effettuiamo  consegne di materiale preparato dal nostro personale interno. Disponiamo inoltre di un magazzino specifico per porte e blindati, con migliaia di prodotti a stock; tutto ciò ci consente di garantire un servizio di qualità, puntuale e personalizzato secondo le specifiche esigenze di ogni cliente. Effettuiamo la duplicazione di molte chiavi, con l’utilizzo di macchinari di ultima generazione. Garantiamo la posa in opera delle nostre porte e le uscite dei nostri tecnici per accertarci preventivamente delle misure. Il nostro magazzino è inoltre dotate di uno scaffale elettronico che facilita e minimizza il tempo nel servire il cliente. PARTE DEL CONSORZIO DIALFER @consorziodialfer

Company description: Praktis е верига строителни хипермаркети, посветена на това да предложи всичко необходимо за строителство, ремонт и обзавеждане, за да улесни живота на професионалисти и любители, които искат най-доброто за своето пространство. Компанията бързо и целенасочено се развива в сегмента “направи си сам” (DIY – Do It Yourself) и е член на European DIY Retail Assosiation/Global Home Improvement Network - EDRA/GHIN . Praktis е история на мечти, амбиции и неуморна работа, която се разгръща в продължение на 22 години. От самото си начало, ние сме се ангажирали да бъдем не просто доставчик на строителни и интериорни решения, а истински партньор в реализирането на проекти за дома и градината. Вярваме, че всеки дом е отражение на индивидуалността на неговите обитатели и нашата роля е да помогнем на тези мечти да станат реалност. С течение на времето, ние сме се утвърдили като важен участник на пазара, стремейки се да предложим не само качествени продукти, но и иновации, които променят начина, по който хората взаимодействат с пространствата около тях. Нашата цел не е просто да продаваме стоки, а да помагаме на нашите клиенти да създадат уютни и функционални пространства, където могат да прекарат незабравими моменти. Поставяме акцент на детайлите, защото знаем, че те правят разликата между обикновеното и изключителното. Днес веригата строителни хипермаркети е представена в 7 български града – София, Пловдив, Велико Търново, Русе, Хасково, Стара Загора, Видин в които има 8 физически магазина и предлага над 50 000 артикула за дома, градината и строителството. Нашият асортимент от разнообразни продукти съчетава достъпност и високи стандарти, осигурявайки на нашите клиенти, решение, което е едновременно практично и естетично, за да им помогнем да реализират своите идеи с лекота и увереност. Ние вярваме, че качеството не е лукс, а необходимост, която всеки заслужава. Ние сме дълбоко ангажирани с корпоративната и социалната отговорност, които считаме за важен аспект от нашата работа.

Company description: The DingzShop.com online store was an e-commerce website that operated domestically in Norway between September 2013 and December 2015. The company was founded by 15-year-old Tobias Mikalsen as a subsidiary of Mikalsen Operations ENK, and sold consumer gadgets such as smartphone accessories and minor home-improvement products, as well as consumer electronics such as projectors, simple smartphones, and home security systems. Operations were winded down in the latter half of 2015. The company announced through its website in November 2015 that the e-commerce store would close down domestic operations temporarily in early December 2015, and were expecting to relaunch with a global approach sometime in mid-2016. Dingzshop.com closed for business on December 10, 2015, and remains closed. Plans to relaunch the e-commerce store has been removed from its website and the website of its parent company, Mikalsen Operations.
